This article first appeared at southern weekend and is not to be reprinted without permission

By He Jiawen, southern weekend correspondent

Southern weekend intern, Ren Huanxin

Editor in chief | Qian Haoping

February 3,2020, the 10th day of the first lunar month. Beijing is bracing for the first working day of the holiday, which is three days longer than usual because of the new outbreak of pneumonia.

Around 9:00 pm, the Beijing Municipal Party Committee, the municipal government through the government's official website issued a letter to the people of the city, point out the epidemic prevention and control into a key stage. As of 2400 hours on February 4,253 cases of new pneumonia had been confirmed in Beijing. That's 25 more than the day before.

From the confirmed cases, compared with other provinces and cities, Beijing is not too many, but confirmed cases and the proportion of the total population has been higher than Guangdong and Zhejiang, epidemic prevention and control is not serious.

As the National Political Center, Beijing's epidemic prevention has its particularity. "Beijing, as the capital, will begin a series of key work and major activities after the start of the year, " the Beijing Municipal Party Committee and the municipal government said in the letter. "We must not slacken our efforts in any way or make any mistakes. "

Soon after the outbreak, Beijing announced that it would cancel temple fairs during the Spring Festival, cancel the first test of the Beijing Winter Olympics, suspend inter-provincial passenger transport, delay the start of school, delay construction... However, as the number of people returning to Beijing after the festival has increased, the prevention and control of the epidemic in Beijing has faced a new challenge.

1
Renovation of "Xiaotangshan"

1

###Renovation of "Xiaotangshan"

"resolutely win the prevention and control of the epidemic, " "seven days and seven nights to build Xiaotangshan SARS hospital to highlight the style of the Iron Army, then assume the mission to fully safeguard the capital safety practice of state-owned enterprises. ". Banners with different slogans hang outside the e district building of the rehabilitation center of Beijing Xiaotangshan Hospital on Feb. 4.

With the spread of the disease from Wuhan to the country, before the Lunar New Year, Xiaotangshan Hospital rehabilitation work has started.

On January 24, Xiaotangshan Hospital issued a statement that no new cases of pneumonia have been admitted, but some wards will be upgraded in the near future in order to improve the environment and conditions of admission. Southern weekend reporters repeatedly called Xiaotangshan Hospital, asked whether the transformation is necessary to prevent and control the epidemic, was the response to "such as health notice. ".

On January 29, a source from the Public Health Office of the Beijing Municipal Commission of Health and hygiene told southern weekend reporters that, "according to epidemic prevention practices, as Beijing is the capital, under the pressure of any major public health emergency, the prevention and control efforts in the capital will only be greater than in other places. "

A doctor at a Beijing city-level designated hospital told southern weekend that his hospital had sent doctors to Xiaotangshan Hospital to "inspect the environment. ".

"Xiaotangshan" in 2003"SARS" period for Beijing Epidemic Prevention has made great contributions. Xiaotangshan Hospital, built in 7 days, has treated 680 SARS patients in 51 days, 8 died, the case fatality rate is less than 1.2% , the lowest in the world, and 1,383 medical staff have not been infected.

After the end of "SARS" , the existence and abolition of Xiaotangshan Hospital has been controversial for a period of time. Finally, the former Beijing Municipal Health Bureau announced in April 2010 that the SARS ward of Xiaotangshan Hospital would be dismantled. Before this epidemic comes, small Tang Shan hospital already changed name to small Tang Shan convalescent hospital.

Ten years later, the hospital has become the focus of attention because of an epidemic that has spread across the country.

On January 30, Lei Haichao, director of the Beijing Municipal Commission of Public Health, responded to media reports that the Xiaotangshan Hospital building is old and needs to be renovated to provide better conditions for medical treatment, to be opened as a supplement to the changes in the epidemic situation.

2
Shall we seal the city?

2

###Shall we seal the city?

Xiaotangshan Hospital is still under repair, and the number of confirmed cases in Beijing is increasing every day. What we need to prepare for now is how to meet the coming back peak.

From the start of the Spring Festival travel rush to Feb. 2, more than 10 million people left Beijing by rail and Civil Aviation. As of Feb. 2, about 2 million people had returned to Beijing, and about 8 million had not returned.

How to control and screen the flow of people returning to Beijing is a big problem Beijing faces.

From January 22, before the festival, the Beijing West Railway Station has started to take the temperature of the incoming and outgoing passengers. Beijing also became the first city, after Wuhan, to set up a temperature checkpoint in and out of the city's fortresses.

Beijing new pneumonia epidemic prevention and control work is also from this day began to spread out in an all-round way. On the same day, Beijing established a new pneumonia epidemic prevention and control leading group, Municipal Party Secretary Cai Qi as the leader of the group, Mayor Chen Jining as deputy group leader. The first meeting of the Leading Group made it clear that it was necessary to "maintain social stability in the capital" .

As of 18:00 on the 22nd, 14 cases of new coronary pneumonia had been confirmed in Beijing.

As the number of confirmed cases increases, Beijing's traffic checkpoints continue to shrink. On January 25, the media received news from the Beijing Municipal Commission of Transport that, starting from January 26, the operating long-distance passenger transport routes to and from Beijing will be suspended, excluding cross-city bus routes and tour charters. The resumption time will be announced separately.

The move has made people living in Beijing nervous, as Wuhan has been "sealed off" and they fear Beijing will follow suit.

On the 26th, the Transport Commission officially announced that it was the second day of the Lunar New Year, but many people who left Beijing had already returned to Beijing in an emergency and shared their news through wechat friends. They changed their flights and train schedules for fear of being "late and unable to come back. ".

Some civil servants in Beijing are also nervous about the announcement, though their concerns are different. Zhang Jun, a grass-roots civil servant, said under a pseudonym that he had "done nothing but stare at his mobile phone" that day. Colleagues were discussing on wechat groups whether they would ask for an early return to their posts in Beijing, after all, Tianjin had already asked civil servants to return to their posts early. The news he eventually received was that he would arrange his own return to Beijing before the start date.

Residents of the "closed city" worry still does not resolve, in the face of rumors, January 26 evening, the Beijing Municipal Transportation Commission Deputy Director Rong Jun at the press conference a Hammer: "No closed city, will not close the city. "

However, there are some restrictions on the means of transport, transportation, can effectively block the transmission of the virus channel. Liu Xiaoming, vice minister of Transport, specifically explained at a press conference held by the State New Office on January 26 that long-distance passenger traffic in Beijing had originally been suspended from the first day to the fourth day of the first lunar month and resumed on the fifth lunar month. "Now this work has been suspended. ".

Beijing has also suspended many flights, some temporary suspension of train services. Between January 28 and February 26, the Beijing Railway Bureau stopped 38 trains. On January 30, Beijing Capital International Airport cancelled 546 flights between Wuhan, Xiangyang, Guangzhou and Shanghai.

Prior to this, the Beijing Municipal Education Commission took the lead in deciding that the universities, middle and primary schools, kindergartens, off-campus training institutions to postpone the start of school. "No student can return to Beijing in advance for any reason, " a Beijing University student said in a Wechat Post

3
It's not easy to get back to Beijing

3

###It's not easy to get back to Beijing

Although the city was not sealed off, what Zhang Jun did not expect was that after he returned to Beijing on January 30, he was stopped at the gate of his residential area. He lives in Tujingjiayuan, in Wangzhen, northwest of Haidian District, and has been ordered by the residents'committee to quarantine himself for 14 days and issue a health certificate before moving in.

Zhang Jun was not the only one who was stopped. On those two days, many "Beipiao" complained in wechat circles that it was not easy to return to Beijing, and some places even took the extreme measure of closing off villages and roads.

During the war "epidemic" in recent days, Beijing repeatedly emphasized the important role of community prevention and control, and reiterated its urgency several times when it was near the peak of returning to Beijing.

Beijing Epidemic Prevention and Control Work Leading Group on January 30, an additional community prevention and control group. The day before that, the pilot program for prevention and control work in community villages formulated by the Leading Group clearly pointed out that community prevention and control should be implemented in group prevention and control, Joint Prevention and control, grid and carpet management.

A street worker in Chaoyang District told southern weekend that they had received the plan that night, and stepped up the deployment of community prevention and control work specifically for returning Beijing residents.

In fact, in January 28, the Beijing Municipal Government issued a notice on the further work of epidemic prevention has pointed out: "The city gradually increased the number of confirmed cases, the epidemic from the importation into the spread of signs. ". The return to Beijing after the Spring Festival is coming, and epidemic prevention is at a critical juncture."

Zhang Ge, deputy director of the Organization Department of the Beijing Municipal Party Committee, also stressed: "district leaders should cover streets and townships, and members of the sub-district township team should cover communities and villages, so that 333 sub-district townships and more than 7,000 communities and villages will be covered. "

Fortunately, the stalemate between the returnees and the street office eased on January 31. Zhao Jigui, deputy director of the Beijing Civil Affairs Bureau, said at a news conference on the th that people returning to Beijing with no symptoms of the epidemic can enter the community normally, but they should wear masks, take body temperatures and take precautions.

But there are also communities that are too strict in their enforcement, Zhao said. "We will dissuade them in time and let them correct, " he said, "without causing panic or bringing about invisible pressure. ".

But police stations, street offices and community health centers are not relieved. Chaoyang District Party Committee began "knock on the door action" , as of February 2 at 24:00, the district visited 1.55 million households, the number of visitors 3878534 people, the basic realization of all know.

"A thousand lines above us, a needle under us, " said the Chaoyang District Street worker, pointing to a stack of documents on his desk. "It's only 10 days. ... Files are coming in every day. There's a lot of pressure on the ground."

"Beijing, as the capital, can not be sloppy in its community epidemic prevention work, " Zhao said. "mutual support is the mass basis for winning this epidemic prevention war. "

Since February 3, Beijing has no longer required people without contact history in Hubei to stay home for 14 days before going to work.
